  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Clinicians should appreciate the effectiveness of virtual reality (VR) headsets for managing&#xD;
      both the anxiety and the behaviour of dental patients. The aim of this study was to assess&#xD;
      the effectiveness of using a VR headset as a distraction for managing the anxiety and&#xD;
      behaviour of patients during their dental treatment related to underlying psychological&#xD;
      factors.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
